협공(cooperative defense) reaction window — fixed
The bug: attack actions carried an attacker-supplied blockers field — meaning the attacker decided whether the defender got to cooperate. Since no attacker would voluntarily hand the defender backup, 협공 was effectively dead in real play (a known issue already flagged in memory).

The fix, mirroring the engine's existing 지략 opt-in reaction pattern:

attack now only carries attackerId/targetId (actions.ts).
If the defender has eligible adjacent allies (new coopBlockersFor query), the engine pauses (state.pendingAttack) and returns an attackReactionRequest instead of resolving immediately (gameCore.ts).
The defender responds with a new resolveAttack action (blockerIds: string[], empty = solo defense).
src/client (App.ts/InteractionLayer.ts) was rewired to consume this properly — the old client-side interception hack that pre-empted attacks before reaching the engine is gone; the engine now owns the reaction.
